===Definitions===
# to [[serve]]

The very Chinese character rootedly<!--What does "rootedly" mean in this context?--> means to serve and to accompany at the same time. Meanwhile, it makes up relative words as follows.

* [[侍从]]: shicong, servants of the emperor or officials.
* [[侍奉]]: shifeng, to serve.
* [[侍候]]: shihou, to serve in a more respectul way with an implication of waiting ([[侯]]).
* [[侍郎]]: shilang, a title of a sort of ancient official.
* [[侍弄]]: shinong, to detail.

